1
00:00:06,027 --> 00:00:07,570
[rhythmic beats playing]

2
00:00:09,030 --> 00:00:10,281
[coffee maker rattling]

3
00:00:10,781 --> 00:00:13,409
-What do you mean, you don't know?
-I don't… I don't know.

4
00:00:13,492 --> 00:00:16,746
I went to bed.
I woke up. Yusuf was gone, okay?

5
00:00:16,829 --> 00:00:20,041
He left us the keys to the truck
and directions to the barn.

6
00:00:20,124 --> 00:00:21,042
That's it.

7
00:00:21,125 --> 00:00:22,376
Are you paying attention?

8
00:00:22,460 --> 00:00:25,671
You put this down, boom,
pick one, then you do the cup.

9
00:00:26,505 --> 00:00:27,339
Thank you.

10
00:00:27,423 --> 00:00:28,382
[Morgan] Oh!

11
00:00:28,883 --> 00:00:30,426
[loud crash]

12
00:00:30,509 --> 00:00:31,552
[pieces clattering]

13
00:00:31,635 --> 00:00:35,014
[yells] Who just disappears
for no reason, huh?

14
00:00:35,097 --> 00:00:39,727
Um… All I can think of, uh, is that,
you know, he seemed upset.

15
00:00:39,810 --> 00:00:41,687
Hm? What do you mean, upset?
Upset with whom?

16
00:00:41,771 --> 00:00:45,483
Me? We just proved
a new fucking drug route.

17
00:00:45,566 --> 00:00:49,361
I think he was just upset
about, like, his girlfriend or something.

18
00:00:49,445 --> 00:00:50,738
How do you know that?

19
00:00:50,821 --> 00:00:52,490
-[Ivan] Andrei.
-[Andrei] Hmm.

20
00:00:52,573 --> 00:00:53,449
Find him.

21
00:00:53,949 --> 00:00:54,992
[Andrei] Okay.

22
00:00:55,076 --> 00:00:56,494
[insects chirping]

23
00:00:57,036 --> 00:00:58,120
[inhales sharply]

24
00:00:58,204 --> 00:01:00,414
[inhales] When the fuck did you get
this information?

25
00:01:01,791 --> 00:01:04,543
We talked the night before.

26
00:01:04,627 --> 00:01:05,503
And?

27
00:01:06,921 --> 00:01:09,924
Come on. Come on, spit it out,
you stupid bitch.

28
00:01:10,007 --> 00:01:11,842
Hey, relax.

29
00:01:11,926 --> 00:01:13,052
[chair scraping]

30
00:01:14,845 --> 00:01:15,971
[Morgan] Oh my God.

31
00:01:16,055 --> 00:01:20,309
[Ivan] Yusuf fucking up this whole thing
for a stupid girl? I mean…

32
00:01:20,392 --> 00:01:24,271
See, he doesn't understand
how easy it is for us to find him. Huh?

33
00:01:26,232 --> 00:01:28,567
Might need you two
to… to… to come to Miami

34
00:01:28,651 --> 00:01:29,944
to finish the deal.

35
00:01:30,027 --> 00:01:31,112
Uh… No.

36
00:01:32,279 --> 00:01:34,031
What did you just say to me?

37
00:01:34,115 --> 00:01:36,200
I just said no, okay?

38
00:01:36,283 --> 00:01:39,036
We have done enough for you.

39
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:43,499
I have been a very good "friend" to you,

40
00:01:43,582 --> 00:01:47,002
and all I've gotten in return
is a fucking slap in the face

41
00:01:47,086 --> 00:01:50,297
and this deep, gross feeling

42
00:01:50,381 --> 00:01:53,551
like I have just betrayed
everything I stand for.

43
00:01:54,343 --> 00:01:57,221
Our father is the former chief of police.

44
00:01:57,304 --> 00:02:02,268
Our mother is a very public person
in this town at the moment, okay?

45
00:02:02,351 --> 00:02:04,353
There are a lot of eyes on us right now.

46
00:02:04,854 --> 00:02:07,273
We are not gonna go running our mouths.
We're not that stupid,

47
00:02:07,356 --> 00:02:10,025
despite what my sister might indicate
a lot of the time.

48
00:02:10,109 --> 00:02:14,905
So we're gonna be walking out of here,
and you are gonna let that happen.

49
00:02:16,365 --> 00:02:18,492
Don't you fucking dare.

50
00:02:20,536 --> 00:02:21,954
[dramatic music playing]

51
00:02:22,746 --> 00:02:24,248
-Hey.
-Morgan, fuck!

52
00:02:24,331 --> 00:02:26,292
-[Morgan] Yeah.
-[Andrei] You want coffee or no?

53
00:02:26,375 --> 00:02:27,585
[Ivan] Hey.

54
00:02:29,170 --> 00:02:30,254
You sure about this?

55
00:02:30,337 --> 00:02:31,922
[Andrei in Russian] Kill him!

56
00:02:32,006 --> 00:02:34,133
[Ivan] Kill him yourself if it's easy!

57
00:02:34,216 --> 00:02:36,760
[Andrei] Come on, give me the gun.
Give me the gun then.

58
00:02:36,844 --> 00:02:40,514
[Ivan speaking Russian]

59
00:02:40,598 --> 00:02:41,974
[Andrei speaking Russian]

60
00:02:42,057 --> 00:02:43,392
[in English] Fuck! Fuck!

61
00:02:43,475 --> 00:02:45,519
[Nicky] Get in the car.
Get in the car right now.

62
00:02:45,603 --> 00:02:47,271
Why wouldn't you have told me about Yusuf?

63
00:02:47,354 --> 00:02:48,981
[Morgan] I didn't think it was important.

64
00:02:49,064 --> 00:02:51,775
[Nicky] Why, because you slept with him
or something fucking messy?

65
00:02:51,859 --> 00:02:54,862
Do you know that you complicate
everything and everyone that you touch?

66
00:02:54,945 --> 00:02:55,821
[engine starting]

67
00:02:55,905 --> 00:02:58,157
I have given us both
a fresh start here, okay?

68
00:02:58,240 --> 00:03:00,326
And I need you to take that
and run with it.

69
00:03:00,409 --> 00:03:02,494
And I would like to kindly ask
that from here on out,

70
00:03:02,578 --> 00:03:04,288
you stay away from me.

71
00:03:04,371 --> 00:03:05,456
[frenetic music playing]

72
00:03:05,539 --> 00:03:06,415
Happily.

73
00:03:07,166 --> 00:03:09,960
-What are you doing? Oh my God!
-I am staying away from you.

74
00:03:10,044 --> 00:03:12,796
-As far as I can go, right now.
-Okay. All right.

75
00:03:12,880 --> 00:03:14,506
-[Morgan] Hope that works.
-Yeah, it does.

76
00:03:14,590 --> 00:03:16,842
-[gravel crunching]
-[tires screeching]

77
00:03:19,553 --> 00:03:20,638
[music ends]

78
00:03:21,222 --> 00:03:23,849
[opening theme music playing]

79
00:03:28,437 --> 00:03:29,772
[music ends]

80
00:03:29,855 --> 00:03:32,149
-[dogs barking]
-[birds chirping]

81
00:03:34,193 --> 00:03:35,444
[exhales]

82
00:03:38,906 --> 00:03:40,241
[Tareq inhales]

83
00:03:41,617 --> 00:03:43,619
-[Nicky exhales]
-[Tareq breathes deeply]

84
00:03:45,663 --> 00:03:48,999
This might be the most uncomfortable
mattress I've ever slept on.

85
00:03:49,083 --> 00:03:52,169
-I wanna be your date to the gala.
-You are my date.

86
00:03:52,253 --> 00:03:55,297
No, I mean your actual date.

87
00:03:56,215 --> 00:04:00,344
Out and Loud is recognizing you
for being great,

88
00:04:00,427 --> 00:04:04,598
and I don't want you standing up there
knowing that we're hiding this away.

89
00:04:06,433 --> 00:04:09,687
-You sure?
-[inhales deeply] Yeah, I am.

90
00:04:09,770 --> 00:04:13,107
It's not fair to you,
and it's not fair to the congregation.

91
00:04:13,816 --> 00:04:14,900
It's time.

92
00:04:15,609 --> 00:04:16,777
It's been time.

93
00:04:18,570 --> 00:04:22,700
I can't believe I'm saying this,
but I am excited to go on a cruise.

94
00:04:22,783 --> 00:04:24,743
-[exhales]
-[Nicky laughs]

95
00:04:28,122 --> 00:04:29,540
[Nicky exhales deeply]

96
00:04:30,582 --> 00:04:32,001
-I'm proud of you.
-Mmm.

97
00:04:32,710 --> 00:04:34,044
-Want coffee?
-Yes, please.

98
00:04:34,128 --> 00:04:34,962
Okay.

99
00:04:36,297 --> 00:04:37,589
[Nicky exhales]

100
00:04:38,382 --> 00:04:39,383
[exhales sharply]

101
00:04:39,883 --> 00:04:42,011
-[door opening]
-[woman screaming]

102
00:04:42,094 --> 00:04:44,263
[woman] Who are you?
What are you doing here?

103
00:04:44,346 --> 00:04:45,180
Rose!

104
00:04:45,264 --> 00:04:47,182
-[Rose] Reverend Dardano, is that what…
-Rose!

105
00:04:47,266 --> 00:04:50,477
-[Tareq] Nicky, come out here, please.
-How did you get into my house?

106
00:04:50,561 --> 00:04:53,981
[woman over podcast] The only thing
keeping you from the life you deserve

107
00:04:54,064 --> 00:04:54,982
is you.

108
00:04:55,607 --> 00:04:58,652
In order to change
the frequency of your life…

109
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:02,364
-[faucet squeaking]
-…you must embrace positive affirmations.

110
00:05:02,448 --> 00:05:04,491
I know this might sound corny,

111
00:05:05,326 --> 00:05:06,285
but it works.

112
00:05:06,368 --> 00:05:07,536
[Morgan sighs, sniffles]

113
00:05:07,619 --> 00:05:10,497
-"I am a good, decent person."
-[exhales]

114
00:05:11,081 --> 00:05:14,501
"I deserve good, decent things."

115
00:05:15,419 --> 00:05:18,464
-"I am ready to make that change."
-[breathes deeply]

116
00:05:18,547 --> 00:05:21,258
"I am ready to be that change."

117
00:05:21,342 --> 00:05:25,095
"I am not my past. I am only my present."

118
00:05:25,179 --> 00:05:26,138
[whispers] …my present.

119
00:05:26,221 --> 00:05:28,223
[rapid gunfire]

120
00:05:28,307 --> 00:05:30,184
[siren wailing]

121
00:05:30,267 --> 00:05:32,019
-[gunfire in video game]
-[woman screaming]

122
00:05:32,102 --> 00:05:33,729
-Fuck! Max!
-[male voice in game] Godlike!

123
00:05:33,812 --> 00:05:36,482
If you're gonna be spraying bullets
at homeless women,

124
00:05:36,565 --> 00:05:40,361
can you at least put your headphones on?
I woke up at six to bake these, dude.

125
00:05:40,444 --> 00:05:41,945
Our floors are clean, babe.

126
00:05:42,613 --> 00:05:45,699
-[woman in game] What are you lookin' at?!
-[gunfire continues]

127
00:05:46,450 --> 00:05:47,826
[pan clanging]

128
00:05:47,910 --> 00:05:50,162
-[sirens blaring in game]
-[gunfire in game]

129
00:05:50,245 --> 00:05:51,413
I'm going on a run.

130
00:05:51,497 --> 00:05:53,332
Like, to the grocery store?

131
00:05:53,415 --> 00:05:56,126
No, like… like for exercise.

132
00:05:57,461 --> 00:05:58,462
Why?

133
00:06:00,589 --> 00:06:02,716
Uh, I'm trying something.

134
00:06:03,592 --> 00:06:04,927
[door opens]

135
00:06:05,761 --> 00:06:08,430
-[gunfire in game continues]
-[loud explosion in game]

136
00:06:10,224 --> 00:06:13,185
As many of you know,
I was photographed last week

137
00:06:13,268 --> 00:06:16,605
entertaining three women
on an evening boat ride. [inhales]

138
00:06:16,688 --> 00:06:19,483
A personal choice
my opponent Linda Morelli

139
00:06:19,566 --> 00:06:21,527
seems to have taken issue with. [inhales]

140
00:06:21,610 --> 00:06:24,446
But let me reassure you all
that my personal life

141
00:06:24,530 --> 00:06:27,408
has never stood in the way
of my leadership abilities.

142
00:06:27,491 --> 00:06:29,576
[over speaker] "Family first," she says.

143
00:06:29,660 --> 00:06:31,495
What about this town first?

144
00:06:31,578 --> 00:06:33,997
And to that point,
what if you don't have a family?

145
00:06:34,081 --> 00:06:35,833
-Then what, Linda?
-[Linda sighs]

146
00:06:35,916 --> 00:06:39,002
[Tom] Sure, I make bold choices
and take big swings.

147
00:06:39,086 --> 00:06:42,172
But it's that kind of attitude that
gets you the big boats in the first place.

148
00:06:42,256 --> 00:06:43,215
[Linda] Mm-hmm.

149
00:06:43,298 --> 00:06:48,011
[Tom] So while Linda Morelli focuses on
jungle gyms and kindergarten classes,

150
00:06:48,095 --> 00:06:52,141
I'll be out here continuing to take
big swings for the people of this town.

151
00:06:52,224 --> 00:06:55,644
From my family to yours,
I'll see you at the polls.

152
00:06:55,727 --> 00:06:59,148
He was caught with three hookers
on a boat. Suddenly, it's my problem.

153
00:06:59,231 --> 00:07:01,024
They're called sex workers.

154
00:07:01,108 --> 00:07:04,194
People are gonna see right through this.
They're gonna see right through it.

155
00:07:04,278 --> 00:07:06,655
Can you imagine the audacity?

156
00:07:06,738 --> 00:07:09,283
Is this illegal?
Honey, why are you wearing a suit?

157
00:07:09,366 --> 00:07:11,577
The campaign barbecue invite
said family-friendly.

158
00:07:11,660 --> 00:07:13,704
I know, and that's what
I wanted to talk to you about

159
00:07:13,787 --> 00:07:16,623
before you forced me
to watch that insane video.

160
00:07:16,707 --> 00:07:18,250
-Um, I--
-[Linda] Well, what?

161
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:21,503
I was wanting to wait
until after the campaign to tell you this,

162
00:07:21,587 --> 00:07:23,505
but it can't wait anymore, so I--

163
00:07:23,589 --> 00:07:25,507
You're sick. It's cancer.
Natalie, is it cancer?

164
00:07:25,591 --> 00:07:26,467
I… I don't know.

165
00:07:26,550 --> 00:07:29,470
It's not cancer, okay?
I don't have cancer.

166
00:07:29,553 --> 00:07:31,305
-I… I, um…
-Oh no. Oh God.

167
00:07:35,476 --> 00:07:36,518
I…

168
00:07:37,561 --> 00:07:38,604
met someone.

169
00:07:38,687 --> 00:07:39,813
[Linda gasps]

170
00:07:39,897 --> 00:07:40,898
[whispers] Nicky!

171
00:07:40,981 --> 00:07:43,025
-And I'm leaving the church.
-Oh.

172
00:07:43,609 --> 00:07:46,320
-[Linda] Whoa.
-And I'm… I'm telling you now

173
00:07:46,403 --> 00:07:50,532
because Rose caught us this morning.

174
00:07:50,616 --> 00:07:52,576
So it has sort of… [inhales]

175
00:07:52,659 --> 00:07:55,287
-[quietly] What?
-…expedited the process a little bit.

176
00:07:55,370 --> 00:07:59,750
And I am… I am going to be his date today
to a very important event,

177
00:07:59,833 --> 00:08:02,085
so I'm gonna be late for the barbecue.

178
00:08:02,169 --> 00:08:04,004
And I… I just wanted to tell you this

179
00:08:04,087 --> 00:08:07,007
and… and let you know
that everything is under control, okay?

180
00:08:07,090 --> 00:08:10,636
-And… and I am good and I am happy, okay?
-[Natalie] Mmm.

181
00:08:10,719 --> 00:08:13,639
[inhales] So, this is obviously something
we're gonna need to get ahead of.

182
00:08:13,722 --> 00:08:16,016
That was the support I was looking for,
thank you so much.

183
00:08:16,099 --> 00:08:17,851
-[Linda] No, Nicky, don't do that.
-Do what?

184
00:08:17,935 --> 00:08:21,230
Expect the clouds to part because
somebody caught you with your pants down.

185
00:08:21,313 --> 00:08:25,567
Your sister and I are waist-deep
in fending off political attacks.

186
00:08:25,651 --> 00:08:29,029
So who is this boyfriend,
this man that you met?

187
00:08:29,112 --> 00:08:30,697
[Linda breathes deeply]

188
00:08:30,781 --> 00:08:32,199
[hammering outside]

189
00:08:32,282 --> 00:08:33,617
It's Tareq Rivera.

190
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:35,202
[inhales] My Tareq?! [laughs]

191
00:08:35,285 --> 00:08:37,454
Well, I don't think--
Yeah, I don't think you can--

192
00:08:37,538 --> 00:08:39,289
-[inhales] Oh!
-He comes into the store.

193
00:08:39,373 --> 00:08:41,583
It doesn't mean
you can claim him as yours.

194
00:08:41,667 --> 00:08:43,961
-Oh, Nick, you have got to be kidding me.
-Yeah.

195
00:08:44,044 --> 00:08:48,715
Choosing this moment when I can't give
this the amount of attention that I want.

196
00:08:48,799 --> 00:08:51,426
How long have you been
hiding this from me?

197
00:08:51,510 --> 00:08:54,680
Finally, a man in the family
who can work with his hands. [laughs]

198
00:08:54,763 --> 00:08:56,139
Kevin works with his hands.

199
00:08:56,223 --> 00:08:58,850
-No, Kevin works with computers, Natalie.
-Ah.

200
00:08:58,934 --> 00:09:02,896
Okay, yeah. I just… I… I did not want
to tell you until after the election

201
00:09:02,980 --> 00:09:06,275
because I didn't want any of this
to hurt your campaign in any way.

202
00:09:06,358 --> 00:09:08,694
It might. I'm an ally, but it might.

203
00:09:08,777 --> 00:09:11,280
Okay. And I also didn't want
the entire town to know

204
00:09:11,363 --> 00:09:13,073
before I was ready to share this.

205
00:09:13,156 --> 00:09:14,992
-What are you implying?
-Nothing.

206
00:09:15,075 --> 00:09:19,037
Donna's son, Anthony,
came home from Mykonos last summer

207
00:09:19,121 --> 00:09:22,207
with a raging case of chlamydia
from a "hot tub." It was a bathhouse.

208
00:09:22,291 --> 00:09:26,587
She pays his credit card bills. That is
a secret that I will take to my grave.

209
00:09:26,670 --> 00:09:28,088
Mm-hmm. [inhales deeply]

210
00:09:28,171 --> 00:09:30,299
So as for Tom Donaldson,

211
00:09:30,382 --> 00:09:34,803
I think you just spend the barbecue
laughing with kids, talking to families.

212
00:09:34,886 --> 00:09:37,014
You are the people's pick.

213
00:09:37,097 --> 00:09:37,931
-Yes.
-[Natalie] Yeah?

214
00:09:38,015 --> 00:09:40,100
So let's just focus on showing that
to the people.

215
00:09:40,183 --> 00:09:42,936
Okay, hun, I hope you're right.
Honey, bring Tareq by the store.

216
00:09:43,020 --> 00:09:45,397
-I want to give him the family discount.
-[Nicky] Okay.

217
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:47,482
[funky music playing]

218
00:09:48,025 --> 00:09:48,942
Hmm, uh…

219
00:09:49,026 --> 00:09:50,235
[happy music playing]

220
00:09:50,319 --> 00:09:52,112
[children speaking indistinctly]

221
00:09:52,195 --> 00:09:54,072
-[screaming]
-[laughing]

222
00:09:54,156 --> 00:09:55,532
[man 1] She makes a good point.

223
00:09:55,616 --> 00:09:57,034
She makes a great point.

224
00:09:57,117 --> 00:09:59,620
We tip a waitress.
Why are we not tipping stewardesses?

225
00:09:59,703 --> 00:10:00,996
-Mmm.
-It's fucking rude.

226
00:10:01,622 --> 00:10:02,956
I think they're union.

227
00:10:04,207 --> 00:10:06,126
I dated a flight attendant
back in college.

228
00:10:07,085 --> 00:10:08,920
-[knocking on door]
-[door opens]

229
00:10:09,004 --> 00:10:10,339
[door squeaking]

230
00:10:11,173 --> 00:10:15,510
Afternoon, gentlemen. I just wanted
to drop this off ahead of schedule.

231
00:10:16,094 --> 00:10:18,972
You can always depend on Ivan
to bring in just what he owes us.

232
00:10:19,056 --> 00:10:20,515
Never over-delivers.

233
00:10:20,599 --> 00:10:21,725
[paper bag rustling]

234
00:10:21,808 --> 00:10:25,646
Tell me, how does it feel to be so good
at just doing the bare minimum?

235
00:10:25,729 --> 00:10:27,147
You get your money?

236
00:10:28,398 --> 00:10:29,399
Yeah, we're good.

237
00:10:30,192 --> 00:10:32,277
[music continues faintly]

238
00:10:32,361 --> 00:10:35,572
Your shoes stuck to the floor?
Get the fuck out of here.

239
00:10:35,656 --> 00:10:38,367
[Ivan] Uh, we're… we're closing the store
for a few days.

240
