he's, uh, stepping down. Oof.

477
00:19:48,333 --> 00:19:49,792
Poor kid. [inhales]

478
00:19:49,876 --> 00:19:53,213
But I guess that's what happens
when you grow up in a broken home.

479
00:19:53,296 --> 00:19:56,507
[inhales] But by all means, kitty cat,
family first.

480
00:19:56,591 --> 00:19:57,717
-[Tom gasps]
-[Natalie] Oh.

481
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:59,469
-Mom. Run.
-Natalie, get me out of here.

482
00:19:59,552 --> 00:20:01,429
-[Linda] Where do I--
-Legs. I'll carry you.

483
00:20:03,181 --> 00:20:04,933
[Max] Are we gonna talk about it?

484
00:20:05,683 --> 00:20:06,601
About what?

485
00:20:07,101 --> 00:20:10,188
Okay, well, first of all,
you're on birth control.

486
00:20:10,271 --> 00:20:12,815
Why'd you tell Tara that we can't
have kids? That's fucking crazy.

487
00:20:12,899 --> 00:20:15,318
I didn't. I didn't say "we."
I didn't say "we," I said "I."

488
00:20:15,401 --> 00:20:18,154
God forbid anyone think
your dick doesn't work for two seconds.

489
00:20:18,238 --> 00:20:20,490
[inhales] And you know, like,
what if I couldn't have kids?

490
00:20:20,573 --> 00:20:22,116
Okay, but you can.

491
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:25,828
Okay, but she doesn't know that.
She doesn't know what I'm going through.

492
00:20:25,912 --> 00:20:28,039
-What are you going through, Morgan?
-[sighs]

493
00:20:28,122 --> 00:20:30,792
You're running now.
You're baking cupcakes. Like, this is…

494
00:20:30,875 --> 00:20:33,503
I don't know, okay?
I don't know, I'm trying.

495
00:20:34,003 --> 00:20:36,005
-Trying?
-Yeah, I'm trying. I'm trying.

496
00:20:36,089 --> 00:20:40,009
I'm trying to be a better person,
but I can't… I can't be like those people.

497
00:20:40,093 --> 00:20:43,179
-What's wrong with those people?
-Oh my-- Everything! Everything!

498
00:20:43,263 --> 00:20:45,473
It was a fucking game, Morgan.

499
00:20:45,556 --> 00:20:46,808
It was a game.

500
00:20:46,891 --> 00:20:50,103
Have you thought about the fact
that it actually might do you some good

501
00:20:50,186 --> 00:20:51,896
to eat shit from time to time?

502
00:20:51,980 --> 00:20:53,648
Oh… I would eat shit right now

503
00:20:53,731 --> 00:20:56,234
if it prevented me
from turning into those people.

504
00:20:56,317 --> 00:20:58,611
Who do you think you are, Morgan?

505
00:20:58,695 --> 00:21:00,697
-You are losing it.
-[phone buzzing]

506
00:21:00,780 --> 00:21:02,699
Yeah. Have you ever thought about the fact

507
00:21:02,782 --> 00:21:05,952
that maybe everyone else is
fucking losing it, and I've just, like…

508
00:21:06,786 --> 00:21:08,329
I've just stayed the same.

509
00:21:08,413 --> 00:21:09,789
[buzzing continues]

510
00:21:10,790 --> 00:21:13,876
Natalie, I really don't want to hear it,
okay? We're on our way. We're--

511
00:21:16,629 --> 00:21:17,755
She-- She what?

512
00:21:18,548 --> 00:21:19,507
What the fuck?

513
00:21:19,590 --> 00:21:22,260
[funky music playing]

514
00:21:22,343 --> 00:21:24,554
Do you know how much time
it takes me to look like this?

515
00:21:25,138 --> 00:21:28,599
-I can only imagine.
-A lot of fucking time. Too much time.

516
00:21:28,683 --> 00:21:30,393
I'm sorry, uh, I wish
I had more information.

517
00:21:30,476 --> 00:21:31,978
-Oh.
-I'm just as frustrated as you are.

518
00:21:32,061 --> 00:21:34,897
It looks like Teagan took the money
and ran. I don't know what to say.

519
00:21:34,981 --> 00:21:39,110
Not to mention Out Magazine paid 3K for
a table at an event that doesn't exist.

520
00:21:39,193 --> 00:21:42,113
They're in publishing.
Do you think they have that kind of money?

521
00:21:42,196 --> 00:21:46,034
Look, I know you're not the one
that did the scamming, but you're a chair,

522
00:21:46,117 --> 00:21:48,828
and you're right in front of me,
and a person I can yell at.

523
00:21:52,415 --> 00:21:54,625
[people speaking indistinctly]

524
00:21:54,709 --> 00:21:56,711
[seagulls calling]

525
00:22:01,966 --> 00:22:02,967
You okay?

526
00:22:03,968 --> 00:22:08,264
If I never hear the name Teagan
ever again, it'll be too soon.

527
00:22:08,348 --> 00:22:09,807
[Tareq] Not now, Nick.

528
00:22:09,891 --> 00:22:10,808
Okay.

529
00:22:15,063 --> 00:22:17,565
-It's not your fault.
-But it kind of is my fault.

530
00:22:17,648 --> 00:22:18,649
How?

531
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:22,070
How is some asshole
stealing money your fault?

532
00:22:22,153 --> 00:22:24,781
Because there were signs,
and I ignored them.

533
00:22:25,948 --> 00:22:28,284
Was Teagan hard to pin down
from time to time? Yeah.

534
00:22:29,494 --> 00:22:32,538
Did I question on a few occasions
if this person was legit?

535
00:22:32,622 --> 00:22:34,874
Was it weird
their bank was in Estonia? Yeah!

536
00:22:34,957 --> 00:22:38,461
But I was so desperate to offset
my guilt that I looked the other way.

537
00:22:41,339 --> 00:22:42,215
What guilt?

538
00:22:43,341 --> 00:22:45,802
This relationship put me
back in the closet, Nick.

539
00:22:45,885 --> 00:22:48,638
And I'm not blaming you for it.
I was a willing participant.

540
00:22:48,721 --> 00:22:50,807
I would make the jokes too. [inhales]

541
00:22:50,890 --> 00:22:53,393
But it doesn't feel good
to hide this away.

542
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:57,313
I got involved in Out and Loud
so I could stay in this

543
00:22:57,397 --> 00:22:59,774
and not feel like
I was betraying a huge part of who I am.

544
00:22:59,857 --> 00:23:02,026
[indistinct chatter]

545
00:23:05,738 --> 00:23:08,533
Well, there has to be a way
of fixing this, no?

546
00:23:09,325 --> 00:23:11,661
Not unless you know how to get
all those people's money back.

547
00:23:13,121 --> 00:23:15,081
[funky music playing]

548
00:23:16,332 --> 00:23:17,166
[music ends]

549
00:23:17,250 --> 00:23:18,376
[insects chirping]

550
00:23:19,085 --> 00:23:21,379
[Andrei] Former military, ruthless.

551
00:23:21,462 --> 00:23:23,881
Recommendation from a friend inside.

552
00:23:24,674 --> 00:23:26,717
Good. Great.

553
00:23:26,801 --> 00:23:28,094
[opera music playing faintly]

554
00:23:28,177 --> 00:23:31,931
So… you guys think you can handle this?

555
00:23:33,683 --> 00:23:34,892
[speaks Russian]

556
00:23:37,311 --> 00:23:39,063
-Andrei…
-[Andrei sighs]

557
00:23:39,147 --> 00:23:41,190
They… they don't speak English?

558
00:23:41,774 --> 00:23:44,277
So they don't speak English.
They're security.

559
00:23:44,360 --> 00:23:46,279
-[Ivan sighs]
-They don't need to speak English.

560
00:23:46,362 --> 00:23:47,822
You got Yusuf?

561
00:23:47,905 --> 00:23:49,198
Where the fuck is Yusuf?

562
00:23:49,282 --> 00:23:50,283
[breathes heavily]

563
00:23:50,366 --> 00:23:51,492
Istanbul.

564
00:23:52,076 --> 00:23:54,078
-What do you mean?
-He went home.

565
00:23:54,745 --> 00:23:56,539
He use company card to buy a ticket.

566
00:23:56,622 --> 00:23:57,790
[Ivan] He went home?

567
00:23:57,874 --> 00:23:59,000
Business class.

568
00:24:01,127 --> 00:24:03,963
He went home. [chuckles, inhales]

569
00:24:04,046 --> 00:24:08,885
The Brazilians want to meet
our operations team, you fucking moron.

570
00:24:08,968 --> 00:24:11,679
-Can't just be the two of us.
-Three isn't much better.

571
00:24:11,762 --> 00:24:13,598
Well, three is better than two.

572
00:24:14,223 --> 00:24:18,227
Three people who actually speak English,
who know the route.

573
00:24:18,311 --> 00:24:20,521
Do you have any idea
what the Brazilians will do to us

574
00:24:20,605 --> 00:24:22,273
if they don't think we can handle this?

575
00:24:22,356 --> 00:24:23,524
Yes, kill us.

576
00:24:23,608 --> 00:24:24,859
And if I get killed,

577
00:24:24,942 --> 00:24:27,695
I will make sure you know
you were the reason for it.

578
00:24:27,778 --> 00:24:31,532
I'll get killed too, you fucking idiot,
so what difference will that make?

579
00:24:31,616 --> 00:24:33,075
[Andrei yells]

580
00:24:33,159 --> 00:24:34,452
[opera music playing loudly]

581
00:24:34,535 --> 00:24:36,162
[Andrei yelling in Russian]

582
00:24:38,080 --> 00:24:39,582
-[loud thud]
-[screams]

583
00:24:39,665 --> 00:24:40,833
[music continues]

584
00:24:40,917 --> 00:24:42,502
[both yelling, grunting]

585
00:24:43,377 --> 00:24:45,254
[Ivan screaming]

586
00:24:45,338 --> 00:24:46,839
[loud smack]

587
00:24:46,923 --> 00:24:48,132
[Andrei grunting]

588
00:24:49,300 --> 00:24:51,552
[Ivan screaming]

589
00:24:51,636 --> 00:24:52,929
[screaming continues]

590
00:24:53,804 --> 00:24:55,097
[music ends]

591
00:24:55,181 --> 00:24:57,183
[doorbell ringing]

592
00:24:58,017 --> 00:24:59,769
-[grunts softly]
-[Andrei groaning]

593
00:24:59,852 --> 00:25:01,604
-[loud thud]
-[floor squeaking]

594
00:25:01,687 --> 00:25:03,356
[opera music playing faintly]

595
00:25:03,439 --> 00:25:05,733
[door unlocks, creaks open]

596
00:25:05,816 --> 00:25:06,943
[insects chirping]

597
00:25:07,026 --> 00:25:08,986
The fuck are you doing here?

598
00:25:09,487 --> 00:25:10,947
[door slams shut]

599
00:25:13,074 --> 00:25:16,202
-Who are they?
-None of your fucking business.

600
00:25:16,285 --> 00:25:18,079
-The fuck is he doing here?
-[Ivan] Uh…

601
00:25:18,162 --> 00:25:20,831
-You both wanted us to come to Miami.
-[Ivan] Yeah.

602
00:25:20,915 --> 00:25:22,792
Yeah? [exhales]

603
00:25:22,875 --> 00:25:27,630
I am willing to do that for you
if you do something for me first.

604
00:25:27,713 --> 00:25:30,424
And the girl. We need the girl too.
She's tougher than he is.

605
00:25:30,508 --> 00:25:31,467
All right, well…

606
00:25:31,551 --> 00:25:34,178
And what… what do you need from us?

607
00:25:36,013 --> 00:25:36,931
[exhales]

608
00:25:37,014 --> 00:25:41,561
You know people who can track people down,
you know, make things right?

609
00:25:41,644 --> 00:25:42,645
You need a hit.

610
00:25:42,728 --> 00:25:43,854
-A what?
-[Andrei] A hit.

611
00:25:43,938 --> 00:25:47,191
-You need them to disappear.
-No. No, no, no, no.

612
00:25:47,275 --> 00:25:48,818
I-- There's… [inhales deeply]

613
00:25:48,901 --> 00:25:52,405
There's somebody who has just stolen
a lot of money from a lot of people, okay?

614
00:25:52,488 --> 00:25:56,576
I just need you to find them and do
whatever it takes to get the money back.

615
00:25:56,659 --> 00:25:57,868
Okay? But not a hit.

616
00:25:57,952 --> 00:26:00,371
So… so, I don't know, scare them…

617
00:26:00,955 --> 00:26:03,332
-But without the hit part.
-[Ivan] Mm-hmm.

618
00:26:03,416 --> 00:26:05,126
-[Andrei] You have info on them?
-Yeah.

619
00:26:05,751 --> 00:26:08,921
Then both of you
will have to come to Miami.

620
00:26:09,797 --> 00:26:12,133
-Well, I can only speak for myself.
-[phone buzzing]

621
00:26:12,216 --> 00:26:13,801
[Nicky sighs heavily]

622
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:16,554
Okay, well, if you can let me
take this call,

623
00:26:16,637 --> 00:26:19,181
I could try to convince
"the tougher one" to come.

624
00:26:19,265 --> 00:26:21,392
-[Ivan] Go ahead.
-Morgan, what do you want?

625
00:26:23,477 --> 00:26:24,770
She what?

626
00:26:24,854 --> 00:26:27,023
[funky music playing]

627
00:26:31,319 --> 00:26:32,486
[music ends]

628
00:26:33,195 --> 00:26:35,114
[Annette] Oh, Jesus Christ.

629
00:26:35,197 --> 00:26:38,367
-What is that, an owl?
-It's a fucking possum, Nicky, okay?

630
00:26:38,451 --> 00:26:39,785
It's a goddamn possum.

631
00:26:39,869 --> 00:26:41,829
-You couldn't have washed off the paint?
-Morgan!

632
00:26:41,912 --> 00:26:44,415
Do you not think we thought about that?
It's not water-soluble.

633
00:26:44,498 --> 00:26:46,334
If we tried, it would only make it worse.

634
00:26:46,417 --> 00:26:49,920
Well, there's nothing we can fucking do
about it now, okay? So, enough.

635
00:26:50,004 --> 00:26:51,297
[Linda sighs heavily]

636
00:26:51,922 --> 00:26:55,176
[Annette] Here's what's gonna happen.
I am going to walk you down those steps,

637
00:26:55,259 --> 00:26:58,429
past the press, and into the car, okay?

638
00:26:58,512 --> 00:26:59,597
[Linda] Yeah.

639
00:26:59,680 --> 00:27:01,682
That's what we're gonna do.
Is everybody clear?

640
00:27:01,766 --> 00:27:03,476
-[Natalie] Mm-hmm.
-Okay.

641
00:27:04,685 --> 00:27:07,021
You've worked way too hard
for this to derail you now, Linda.

642
00:27:07,104 --> 00:27:08,397
Yeah.

643
00:27:08,481 --> 00:27:10,399
[inhales] Okay, good, let's go.

644
00:27:10,483 --> 00:27:13,861
Okay, and maybe turn your head away
from the cameras. [inhales]

645
00:27:14,362 --> 00:27:17,114
-[door squeaking]
-[reporters shouting indistinctly]

646
00:27:17,782 --> 00:27:18,908
[reporter] One question!

647
00:27:18,991 --> 00:27:21,327
What do you have to say
about Tom Donaldson?

648
00:27:21,410 --> 00:27:22,828
[cameras clicking]

649
00:27:22,912 --> 00:27:25,956
Mrs. Morelli, care to comment
on the allegations of assault

650
00:27:26,040 --> 00:27:27,249
coming from Mr. Donaldson?

651
00:27:27,333 --> 00:27:28,918
-Bullshit, let it go.
-No, no, assault?

652
00:27:29,001 --> 00:27:30,961
Is that what he's--
Is that what he's calling it?

653
00:27:31,045 --> 00:27:31,879
Okay, sure.

654
00:27:33,297 --> 00:27:34,340
Um…

655
00:27:34,423 --> 00:27:36,217
[inhales] Here's the truth.

656
00:27:36,300 --> 00:27:37,551
[cameras clicking]

657
00:27:37,635 --> 00:27:41,639
There are very few things that
a mother won't do to protect her son,

658
00:27:41,722 --> 00:27:46,811
especially when he's found love
after dedicating two decades of his life

659
00:27:46,894 --> 00:27:47,978
to the church.

660
00:27:48,062 --> 00:27:51,315
You fuck with my family, you fuck with me.

661
00:27:51,399 --> 00:27:53,818
And I'm sorry if that sounds déclassé
or something,

662
00:27:53,901 --> 00:27:56,028
but that's who this mother is.

663
00:27:56,112 --> 00:27:58,739
-See, Tom Donaldson got something…
-Linda, the car's right here.

664
00:27:58,823 --> 00:28:01,200
…very wrong about me.

665
00:28:01,283 --> 00:28:04,870
Yes, my campaign is built on family first,
but the thing is,

666
00:28:04,954 --> 00:28:08,874
I consider this town to be my family,

667
00:28:08,958 --> 00:28:10,793
and I will protect it,

668
00:28:11,335 --> 00:28:14,630
and I will fight for it
with the same maternal instincts

669
00:28:14,714 --> 00:28:18,342
that I did for my son this afternoon.

670
00:28:19,343 --> 00:28:22,054
So if Tom Donaldson

671
00:28:22,138 --> 00:28:26,934
considers a little tap on the nose
from this lowly mother of three assault,

672
00:28:27,017 --> 00:28:29,103
then I'm afraid… [laughs]

673
00:28:29,186 --> 00:28:34,525
…he has totally underestimated
just how powerful my family is.

674
00:28:34,608 --> 00:28:36,944
-[reporter 1] Linda!
-[reporter 2] Linda Morelli!

675
00:28:37,027 --> 00:28:38,738
[reporters clamoring]

676
00:28:39,613 --> 00:28:40,865
[car door opens]

677
00:28:41,615 --> 00:28:44,368
-I need you to come with me to Miami.
-Oh, thank God.

678
00:28:44,452 --> 00:28:46,370
[techno music playing]

679
00:30:10,538 --> 00:30:11,455
[music ends]
